Document: RDUniform
Path: godot/classes/class_rduniform.rst
Summary: Describes the binding and uniform_type properties of the RDUniform class, including their default values and access methods.

binding (int): The uniform's binding. Default: 0. Methods: set_binding(value: int), get_binding() → int.

uniform_type (UniformType): The uniform's data type. Default: 3. Methods: set_uniform_type(value: UniformType), get_uniform_type() → UniformType.
---CHUNK---
Document: RDUniform
Path: godot/classes/class_rduniform.rst
Summary: Methods for managing bound IDs associated with a uniform in the rendering system.

Method: add_id(RID id) → void. Binds the given id to the uniform. The data associated with the id is then used when the uniform is passed to a shader.

Method: clear_ids() → void. Unbinds all ids currently bound to the uniform.

Method: get_ids() → Array<RID> (const). Returns an array of all ids currently bound to the uniform.